@SG_ML_HEADER_setup Setting up SGEXTN
There are no compiled binaries for SGEXTN as supporting all possible operating system and compiler combinations is unfeasible. However, building SGEXTN yourself is really easy.
First ensure that you have CMake (at least version 3.21) available. Then you can simply download the entire repository and open the top level CMakeLists.txt in Qt Creator as a project and click the "build" button 2 spaces below the run button. After that, run the CMake command
@SG_STARTCODEBLK
cmake --install [folder where you find the DLLs] --config Release --prefix [folder where you want to install SGEXTN to]
@SG_ENDCODEBLK
in the Qt Creator terminal and add these to your system PATH.
@SG_STARTCODEBLK
[folder where you want to install SGEXTN to]/lib
[folder where you want to install SGEXTN to]/lib/cmake/SGEXTN
@SG_ENDCODEBLK
Now your computer is ready for building SGEXTN apps. To learn how to build one, see this @SG_ML_L008011tutorial../tutorials/full.
When naming classes in your applications, ensure that the names start with "SG", followed by 3 capital letters indicating your application, followed by the actual class name. This ensures that different developers using SGEXTN would not have conflicting class names and that your application is compatible with SGEXTN tooling.
